; Regression test for issue #1950:
; --average (-A) should compute per-account averages, not a global average
; across all accounts.  With --monthly and multiple accounts in the same
; period, the running count was a global row counter rather than a period
; counter, causing the second account's average to be contaminated by the
; first account's presence in the same period.

2022/01/01 January
    Expenses:Acc1               $100.00
    Assets:Cash

2022/01/15 January
    Expenses:Acc2               $200.00
    Assets:Cash

; Both accounts appear in January (period 1).  With the bug, Acc2 showed
; $150 (= $300 global total / count=2 global rows).  With the fix, both
; accounts use count=1 (one period elapsed) and report their own totals:
; Acc1: $100/1 = $100, Acc2: $200/1 = $200.
test reg --monthly --average ^Expenses
22-Jan-01 - 22-Jan-31           Expenses:Acc1               $100.00      $100.00
                                Expenses:Acc2               $200.00      $200.00
end test
